<br>
The Great Book of hearts &amp; souls....<br>
<br>
this book she carried with her always when she was alone it gave her comfort to know all that she ever came into contact with was written there. But the book only appears when it wants something she thought.<br>
<br>
She took her right hand and lifted the leather binding back into the pages before her. Going to the marked spot where she had left her silk ribbon for her hair. She then grabbed her quill and dipped it gently into the ink on her scribing desk.<br>
<br>
Dear book...you have shown me to yourself once again. I do not know where you lead me or the reasons why. I know in my heart the souls I have come to meet are there, in my heart. Every time I give my heart to a man you come back into my life as if you are telling me ...a cleric I will always be a wife never. <br>
Last time you took me on a journey I was on that journey for over 6 months and before that another 5 months. I hope this journey is short your pages glow with gold I know my journey is not far. But so many wonders I have yet to expereince.  I have written all the names I have ever met in my life in this book ..book!! You tear my heart but yet I must do what I must. My viens burn with fear &amp; sadness but excitment at the same time.<br>
I am yours binded by the soul and I will do your bidding.<br>
<br>
Ophillia closed the book. She stood up and gathered her things. She dressed as a noble healer all polished and new. She  grabbed her book and the note to post on the guild boards.<br>
<br>
She looked before her, once her sisters room and her old room at the end of the hall..&lt;she sniffled&gt; her echo could be heard.<br>
The hall was empty and all were asleep. She walked over to the boads and posted her note made a deep sigh. As she walked passed Keil and Steoff rooms she placed a red rose on eash door step and a letter inside with her seal that it was her.<br>
<br>
She took a last look upwards and looked around...this place is so beautiful my heart breaks hard. The book began to radiate a bright gold with a hint of red. Almost like the book itself bled. It made waves to tell her to move on...OPhillia turned at the great doors, stopped turned around and said I love you Tears please don't hate me too much I do love you all. Ophillia then procedded to walk out gently closing the doors as not to make a sound....The gyspy druid was there waiting for her and in the slight moments that passed the two stepped into a portal in time and vanished into the night.<br>
